Jamie - how do you build your glutes? Is a question I get asked a lot! It‚Äôs not something that‚Äôs happened over night and I didn‚Äôt find what worked for me straight away. So this is the first thing to tackle on the subject BE PATIENT with yourself and your progress we all work at different paces. The quicker you relise that muscle doesn‚Äôt grow over night the less disappointed you‚Äôll be!
-
‚úÖ Progressive overload
This requires a gradual increase of volume in your exercises that can make your exercises more difficult by focusing on volume, intensity, tempo and frequency or even increasing resistance.
-
‚úÖ Exercises
We have to work all of our muscle groups - you can‚Äôt just work your arse all the time. Working all of your muscle groups whether you target one muscle group a day or full body increases your over all strength over time and getting muscle all over! It‚Äôs an all over transformation - and an amazing one at that! Specifically for glutes it‚Äôs good to remember the fundamental exercises squats, lunges, dead lifts and hip thrusts are all good but we also need to include accessory moves to keep that muscle engagement (in this case your glutes) such as kick backs, hip abduction, kettle bell swings, hyper extension are to name but a few!
-
‚úÖ NUTRITION
This part isn‚Äôt rocket science and completely depending on your circumstances and I‚Äôm not going to fluff it up to say you need to x amount of calories to grow muscle as it depends on so many factors! However here are ways you can grow muscle: in a calorie deficit, in your calorie maintenance and in a surplus. There is no magic chicken or fish finger or a specific food that will help. Hit your protein and don‚Äôt worry about the rest so much. If you struggle to hit your protein then grab a protein shake (unless you‚Äôre me and love to eat so much üòÇ). The best thing in this case with your food is not to complicate it. One thing you may notice like I did, is that as I tried new things and worked harder in the gym (lifting heavier for example) I was naturally more hungrier than normal!
-
Be patient with yourself, give yourself some credit, don‚Äôt over complicate ir and go and smash it! ü•∞
